dcterms:description: The dataset provided by the Illinois Department of Public Health (IDPH) contains 133,867 observations from 2008 to 2021. Each observation corresponds to the testing of a particular trap on a particular day. These traps are of the gravid type and collect primarily Culex mosquitoes, although they do occasionally capture Aedes albopictus. Variables include trap latitude and longitude, sample collection day, number of mosquitoes in sample, and test result (positive or negative).
dcterms:title: Illinois Department of Public Health (IDPH) Dataset
